Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at a breakfast event in Washington, D.C., expressing gratitude and unity. She emphasized the importance of faith during difficult times and shared a story about a food bank where people, despite their own struggles, showed kindness and generosity. Harris believes that faith should motivate action and give purpose. She referenced the story of Nehemiah, who inspired people to rebuild Jerusalem through their faith. Harris concluded with a prayer for faith in God and in one another, asking for kindness, generosity, and grace.